element.name: Sidetracked - Donabate by Windsockers, Traditional Cache (1/1.5)

p.b: Donabate railway station is located on the main Dublin-Belfast Railway line.

long-description.p: The station opened in 1844 and boasts an array of Dublin & Drogheda and Great Northern Railway station buildings. The main building, a two storey red bricked type was built prior to GNR take over in the 1870s and is therefore unlike others on the line.
Side-Tracked Caches are intended to provide quick Cache-and-dashes at Train Stations.
The Cache is a small micro container please rehide it well to prevent the many muggles from discovering it.

2010-06-07T19:00:00Z : Found it by niallk1234
The fourth of 6 finds for today, but the edge of the carpark beside the platform where the cache is under construction works, and probably can't be acessed during working hours. Nevertheless I found a gap in the fence and found it easily. Luckily it was bank holiday Monday. Another of the series crossed off, TFTC.
